data.title: Princess Iman weds Jameel Thermiotis
data.meta_description: In the presence of Their Majesties King Abdullah and Queen Rania, HRH Princess Iman married Mr Jameel Alexander Thermiotis on Sunday, March 12, 2023, according to a Royal Court statement.
data.meta_site_name: Jordan News | Latest News from Jordan, MENA
data.text:
AMMAN — In the presence of Their Majesties King Abdullah and Queen Rania, HRH Princess Iman married Mr Jameel AlexanderThermiotis on Sunday, March 12, 2023, according to a Royal Court statement.اضافة اعلان

Their Royal Highnesses Prince El Hassan bin Talal, Crown Prince Hussein, Prince Hashem, Prince Feisal bin Al Hussein, Prince Ali bin Al Hussein, Prince Hashim bin Al Hussein, Prince Talal, Prince Ghazi, and Prince Rashid bin El Hassan attended the wedding, held at Beit Al-Urdun, Their Majesties’ private residence.

Their Royal Highnesses Princess Muna Al Hussein, Princess Basma bint Talal, Princess Salma bint Abdullah, Princess Alia bint Al Hussein, Princess Aisha bint Al Hussein, Princess Zein bint Al Hussein, Princess Raiyah bint Al Hussein, Princess Sarvath El Hassan, Princess Rahma bint El Hassan, Princess Sumaya bint El Hassan, Princess Zeina Al Feisal, Princess Rym Ali, Princess Ghida Talal, Princess Miriam Ghazi, Princess Zeina Rashid, Princess Taghrid Muhammad, and Her Highness Princess Firyal were also in attendance.

Royal family members, as well as members of the Thermiotis family and a number of invited guests attended the wedding.

The Royal Hashemite Court congratulates Their Majesties King Abdullah and Queen Rania on this occasion, and extends its warmest wishes of happiness and prosperity to HRH Princess Iman and Mr Thermiotis, the statement read.
